CTIONAL GARAGE DOOR BUILDING CHARACTERISTICS d H h p Basic dimensions.";i:15;s:288:"H - height of wall opening d - height of the lintel B - width of wall opening ab - width of free area on sides of wall opening h - total height of the garage p - depth of the garage Dimensions to which attention should be paid because of possible conflicts with the mechanism of the gate.";i:16;s:23:"I went from 21m to 24m.";i:17;s:107:"The steel lintel that spans the top of the garage is at ceiling height so that shouldnt need to be changed.";i:18;s:117:"Youll probably just have strips of pine or fibre cement covering the gap between the ceiling and the top of the door.";i:19;s:117:"Well in all probability the lintel will soon no wind load from the door only about a foot of the three feet above it.";i:20;s:145:"I would be far far more concerned with the load from the brick and limiting the deflection of the lintel over the door to keep the door operable.";i:21;s:30:"It looks tight for me as well.";i:22;s:201:"Drop pff height is about 280mm ceiling height should be 2600mm so finished opening would be around 2150-2200 I am leaving 50mm for some accidental mistakes like slab thicknesslevel cover of LVL lintel.";i:23;s:31:"Garage door which is 450mm max.";i:24;s:63:"These studs shall have a maximum height of 9-10 30m OBC 923101.";i:25;s:75:"Studs outside of this parameter shall be addressed on a case by case basis.";i:26;s:150:"Openings in loadbearing walls greater than the required stud spacing shall be framed with lintels designed to carry the superimposed loads OBC 923122.";i:27;s:296:"Generally for a roller door you install the tracks and the support brackets for the curtain roll inside the garage opening for maximum use and in many cases because the average roll size for a roller door is between 300 and 450mm it needs to go behind the lintel to maintain drive through height.";i:28;s:127:"The lintel of a garage is a load-bearing beam that supports the opening in the framing where the